Peru Stocks: Aceros Arequipa, Edegel, Minsur, Pomalca, Volcan

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-04-15T22:12:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-15/peru-stocks-aceros-arequipa-edegel-minsur-pomalca-volcan.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima  General Index rebounded 3.4 percent to 19,371.26.
The MSCI All Peru Capped Index gained 3 percent to 2,610.58.  Industrial stocks and utilities jumped after institutional
investors took advantage of a three-day plunge to pick up cheap
stocks, said Pablo Leno, head of trading at Celfin Capital SAB.  Edegel SA (EDEGELC1 PE), the Peruvian unit of  Spain ’s
Endesa SA, soared 19 percent to 1.61 soles. Empresa
Agroindustrial Pomalca SA (POMALCC1 PE), a unit of Grupo Oviedo,
jumped 14 percent to 48 centimos after the  U.S. Department of
Agriculture  said Peru’s sugar production will rise 13 percent
this year. Luz del Sur (LUSURC1 PE), Peru’s largest electricity
distributor, rose 12 percent to 5.60 soles. Corp. Aceros
Arequipa SA (CORAREI1 PE), the Lima-based steelmaker, climbed
9.4 percent to 2.67 soles.  Precious metals and tin miners advanced after metals
rebounded in New York and  London .  Volcan Cia. Minera SAA (VOLCAAC1 PE), Peru’s largest silver
and zinc producer, gained 10 percent to 4.51 soles. Soc. Minera
El Brocal SAA (BROCALC1 PE), a silver and zinc producer, rose
7.9 percent to 41.35 soles.  Minera IRL Ltd. (MIRL)  , a U.K.
minerals explorer with a gold mine in Peru, gained 7.2 percent
to $1.34.  Minsur SA (MINSURI1)  (MINSURI1 PE), the world’s fourth-largest
tin producer, rose 4.9 percent to 3.41 soles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at   aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
